{{about|the Buffy the Vampire Slayer book|the episode of The Walking Dead|The Suicide King (The Walking Dead)}} {{multiple issues|{{Notability|Books|date=October 2009}}{{no footnotes|date=April 2014}}{{refimprove|date=April 2014}}}} {{Infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> | name = The Suicide King | title_orig = | translator = | image = The Suicide King (Buffy Novel).jpg | caption = First edition cover | author = Robert Joseph Levy | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[United States]] | language = [[English language|English]] | series = Buffy the Vampire Slayer | genre = [[Horror novel]] | publisher = [[Pocket Books]] | release_date = February 8, 2005 | english_release_date = | media_type = Print ([[Paperback]]) | pages = 160 | isbn = 1-4165-0242-4 | oclc= 57199978 | preceded_by = [[How I Survived My Summer Vacation]]<!-- Preceding novel in series --> | followed_by = [[Keep Me in Mind (novel)|Keep Me In Mind]]<!-- Following novel in series --> }} {{Portal |Children's literature}}
'''''The Suicide King''''' is a novel by Robert Joseph Levy. It is based on the [[United States|American]] television series ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer (TV series)|Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]''. The first in the line of ''Buffy'' "Stake your Own Destiny" books, ''Suicide King'' gives the reader a large series of choices. Once a choice is made, the page number to turn to is given. The result is that the reader might decide the fate of the characters.
==Plot summary== A number of student suicides has been taking place at Sunnydale High, shaking the community. Then the new grief counselor ends up killing himself, the Scoobies suspect that there is something supernatural to blame. Soon one of them shows suicidal signs and Buffy must race against time to defeat the ancient "Suicide King".
