{{notability|Products|date=October 2015}} {{Infobox video game |title = Yoostar |developer = [[Blitz Games Studios]] |publisher = Yoostar Entertainment Group |platforms = [[PlayStation 3]], [[Xbox 360]], [[Personal Computer|PC]], [[Macintosh|Mac]] |genre = Casual }} '''''Yoostar''''' is a video-based gaming system developed by Yoostar Entertainment Group that allows users to insert themselves into movie or television scenes to perform with the films' original actors and post the resultant video on the Yoostar web site, as well as in third-party [[social networking]] environments like [[Facebook]], [[YouTube]] or [[MySpace]].<ref>{{Cite web| last = Struck | first = Heather| title = Yoostar's Hollywood Dreams | publisher = Forbes | url = https://www.forbes.com/2009/05/14/yoostar-movies-media-technology-personal-tech-yoostar.html| date = 14 March 2009|archiveurl=https://archive.is/KObo|archivedate=18 September 2012}}</ref> The game is a video [[karaoke]], judging individuals performances.
YooStar Entertainment's first product – ''YooStar 1'', for [[Personal computer|PC]] and [[Macintosh|Mac]] – was initially released in an exclusive marketing partnership with the [[Bloomingdale's]] department store chain on August 26, 2009.<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/yoostar-available-today-in-bloomingdales-stores-nationwide-62062477.html| title = Yoostar Available Today in Bloomingdale's Stores Nationwide | publisher = PR Newswire | date = 26 August 2009}}</ref>
==Gameplay== To populate the ''Yoostar'' clip library, in-house artists digitally erase actors or other key figures in a licensed film or television clip. The company has patented this technique.{{Citation needed|date=October 2015}}The user films him- or herself saying either the original lines from the clip using the software’s teleprompter, or ad-libbing their own version. A chalk outline is overlaid on the scene to help position the user in scale with the other actors. The user is allowed as many takes as needed to get a satisfactory result.<ref>{{Cite web| last = Baig | first = Edward| title = Yoostar lets anyone act opposite Hepburn, Brando | publisher = USA Today | url = https://www.usatoday.com/tech/columnist/edwardbaig/2009-09-02-yoostar_N.htm| date = 2 September 2009}}</ref> The software then composites the user’s filmed content with the original clip in the same fashion Hollywood actors are filmed against [[green screen]]s on set and inserted into digitally created backgrounds. The final product is then labeled and stored on the user's local machine, with the option to upload to Yoostar's website. The site provides the ability to embed content in any [[Adobe Flash|Flash]]-supporting [[HTML]] environment using raw code, or in [[blogging]] platforms and social networking sites such as Facebook. Yoostar site users can rate, comment, and share content with the public or a group of "[[Friend_(Facebook)#Friend|Friends]]," depending on each clip's settings.{{Citation needed|date=October 2015}}
==Yoostar 2== On Tuesday June 15, 2010, to coincide with the beginning of the 2010 [[Electronic Entertainment Expo]], Yoostar announced a second version of the game and launched a new website called ''Yoostar 2''. ''Yoostar 2'' is playable via the [[Xbox 360]] ([[Kinect]] required) and [[PlayStation 3]] ([[PlayStation Eye]] required, [[PlayStation Move]] optional) video game consoles. Yoostar2 includes 80 film scenes from major Hollywood studios.{{Citation needed|date=October 2015}}
''Yoostar 2'', for the [[Xbox 360]] [[Kinect]] and [[PlayStation Move]] released in North America on March 8, 2011. In the fall of 2011, Yoostar cooperated with MTV to allow users to star in scenes from MTV's TV shows and music videos. ''Yoostar on MTV'', for [[Xbox 360]] [[Kinect]] released in North America on November 15, 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/the-release-of-yoostar-on-mtv-for-the-xbox-360-makes-kinect-owners-the-star-in-mtv-shows-and-music-videos-2011-11-15| title=The Release of 'Yoostar on MTV' for the Xbox 360 Makes Kinect Owners the Star in MTV Shows and Music Videos| publisher = MarketWatch, Inc}}</ref>
